\begin_layout Subsubsection
[G4] Allow the users to create an event
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Information of event's description, calendar saved and time must always
 be provided, while the location of the event is optional
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must ask for the description and the location of the appointment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The system must ask whether the event should be time-flexible.
 In this case it must require a time window and how long the appointment
 will last
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Button for repeating an event weekly must be shown
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Button for choosing the calendar in which the event will be saved must be
 shown
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A multiple choice list of available means of transportation must be included
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The button to choose the calendar is, by default, the last calendar chosen,
 or the first calendar if the user has never added an event
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
While creating an event, the system must take into account whether the eco
 mode has been turned on
\end_layout

